<TITLE> One shot dead in the capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 16 (bdnews24.com)A young boy was shot dead over a dispute over love affair with a girl at Banashri in the capital on Friday morning. The victim, Zahirul, 15, was a salesman of Sanchita Store in the locality. Officer-in-charge of Rampura Police Station Ali Ahmed Hashmi said Zahirul picked up a brawl with a local boy just after opening the shop. At one stage, he was shot point blank. Zahirul was rushed to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where the doctors declared him dead. The motive of the murder might be a relation Zahirul had with a girl in the neighbourhood, the officer added. bd
